Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and bilirubinuria, with low urine specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting significant renal dysfunction, possibly acute or chronic kidney disease with impaired concentrating ability. The low HbA1c with glucosuria and ketonuria may indicate recent-onset or poorly controlled diabetes or another metabolic disturbance. Further clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation are strongly recommended.
